description:
Because attributes are becoming immutable, we need to make it easy to get modified copies.  E.g.

{noformat}
$client2 = $client->clone( read_preference => { ... } );
$coll2 = $coll->clone( write_concern => { ... } );
{noformat}

In the most recent MongoDB Perl driver, {{MongoDB::GridFS::File->slurp()}} dies with:

bq. GridFS file corrupt: no chunks found for file ID ...

when fetching empty files.

For example:

{code:perl}
#!/usr/bin/env/perl

use strict;
use warnings;

use FileHandle;

use MongoDB 0.708.1.0;
use MongoDB::GridFS 0.708.1.0;

# ---

my $filename = 'empty_file';
my $empty_data = '';

my $client = MongoDB::MongoClient->new( host => 'localhost', port => 27017 );
my $database = $client->get_database( 'empty_files_db' );
my $gridfs = $database->get_gridfs;

# Store empty file
my $basic_fh;
open( $basic_fh, '<', \$empty_data );
my $fh = FileHandle->new;
$fh->fdopen($basic_fh, 'r');
$gridfs->insert( $fh, { 'filename' => $filename } );

# Read empty file
my $returned_data;
eval {
    my $file = $gridfs->find_one( { 'filename' => $filename } );

    # HERE:
    $returned_data = $file->slurp;
};
if ( $@ ) {
    die "Unable to fetch empty file '$filename': $@\n";
}

print "Data: $returned_data\n";
{code}

Script is expected to print out an empty string, but die()s at {{$file->slurp}} line with:

bq. Unable to fetch empty file 'empty_file': GridFS file corrupt: no chunks found for file ID '5563536ac63e2b64e22f2331'

Older Perl driver versions (e.g. v0.707.1.0) work fine in this case. {{mongofiles}} utility is able to read / write empty files fine as well.

Code:
{code}
#!/usr/bin/perl -w

use MongoDB;
use Tie::IxHash;

my $mongo = MongoDB::MongoClient->new;
my $c = $mongo->get_database('test')->get_collection('t');

tie(%h, 'Tie::IxHash', a => undef, b => 1);
$c->insert(\%h);
{code}

Run:
{code}
$ perl 1.pl
Use of uninitialized value in subroutine entry at /home/and/perl5/perlbrew/perls/perl-5.20.0/lib/site_perl/5.20.0/x86_64-linux/MongoDB/Collection.pm line 235.
Use of uninitialized value in subroutine entry at /home/and/perl5/perlbrew/perls/perl-5.20.0/lib/site_perl/5.20.0/x86_64-linux/MongoDB/Collection.pm line 235.
Use of uninitialized value in subroutine entry at /home/and/perl5/perlbrew/perls/perl-5.20.0/lib/site_perl/5.20.0/x86_64-linux/MongoDB/Collection.pm line 235.
{code}

Result:
{code}
> db.t.find().pretty()
{
	"_id" : ObjectId("5575a796c822c12fa24f41b1"),
	"a" : "",
	"b" : NumberLong(1)
}
> 
{code}

Minimal repro:

{noformat}
use strict;
use warnings;
use Tie::IxHash;
use MongoDB;
my $client     = MongoDB::MongoClient->new;
my $database   = $client->get_database('test');
